    <div class="rfd">
      <div class="nytint-panelists-rail rfd-flat">
        <div class="nytint-intro">
  <h4 class="nytint-sectionHeader">Introduction</h4>

  <div class="w380 right"><img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2017/02/06/opinion/RFD-Uber-boycott/RFD-Uber-boycott-sfSpan.jpg" alt="Uber boycott" /><span class="caption">Last week, protesters gathered outside Uber&#8217;s offices in New York.</span> <span class="credit">Brendan McDermid/Reuters</span></div>

<p><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/31/business/delete-uber.html">Uber</a>, <a href="//www.foxnews.com/food-drink/2017/01/31/trump-supporters-vow-to-boycott-starbucks-over-ceos-plan-to-hire-refugees.html">Starbucks</a>, <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2017/feb/06/super-bowl-ad-prompts-trump-supporters-to-boycott-budweiser">Budweiser</a>. These are just a few of the brands that have faced consumer boycotts for taking supposedly political stances in the past few weeks. Still, it is <a href="//www.marketwatch.com/story/starbucks-boycott-like-most-others-wont-hurt-it-in-the-long-term-2017-02-03">unclear</a> whether most of these boycotts will negatively affect sales or change company policy. </p>

<p>When does &#8220;voting with your wallet&#8221; work?</p>

  
  
</div>
        <div class="columnGroup rfd-ad" id="AdxMiddleRight"></div>
      </div><!-- .nytint-panelists-rail -->
    </div><!-- .rfd -->

  </div><!-- .nytint-grid-container -->

  <div class="rfd">
